  "text": "I n a Lhunderstorm the environment is altered by the presence of N larger particles per unit volume which can capture the small ions (Fletcher 141). The electric field may or may not be involved in the capture of ions. If the electric field is involved we probably have a case of hyperelectrification described by G u m [CITATION_1] and if the field is not involved we can use the recombination coefficient, q , given above.",
